    "Therefore, we can argue that our research can contribute to the cognitive load theory literature from an explainable social media recommendation perspective (Sweller, 2011).",
    "Our research findings contribute to the design theory of implications for explainable recommendation systems (Herm et al., 2022), the scholarly literature on end users' requirement collection, and the attributes of explanation (Liao et al., 2020; Wang et al., 2019).",
    "Additionally, our research adds implications to the explanation of quality dimensions and AI adoption literature (Eagly & Chaiken, 1993; Fazio & Olson, 2007; Haque et al., 2023).",
